t4258.text: Conti was a presence all game. He would ran down either wing or down the middle the first half. After Chierico came on, he ran down the left flank. His shots weren't much of a danger but he was involved in the third goal.

t4259.text: Pruzzo was rarely involved in the first half but he scored the second goal and he dropped back to link up with teammates.

t4260.text: Falcão was superb in his distribution. Dictated the play, remained calm, and made some fine passes.

t4261.text: Graziani scored a well-taken goal after an Ubaldo Righetti long-ball. He did have plenty of other chances to score too and regularly made himself available to teammates.

t4262.text: Cerezo was my MOTM. Ran up and down the ground, excellent in his distribution, and scored the third goal.

t4263.text: With Chierico at RM, Conti went to LM, Maldera went to LB, and Sebastiano Nela switched to RB. This created more overlapping than when Oddi was at RB.

t4264.text: Roma had plenty of chances to score in the first half but they couldn't convert them. The Giallorossi became harder to contain when Odoacre Chierico came on for an injured Emidio Oddi. Liedholm made shuffles on the flanks and it paid off.

t4265.text: Bruno Conti, Falcão, and Toninho Cerezo provided a lot of movement in midfield whereas Aldo Maldera started in a fixed left midfield. Francesco Graziani moved around the final third and would drop back. Roberto Pruzzo was static in the first half but moved more in the second.

t4266.text: Captain Agostino Di Bartolomei still played an attacking role from the centre-back. Initiated attacks, was involved in the third goal, and had a couple of long-range shots near the end.

t4267.text: Roma coach Nils Liedholm lined his team up in a standard 4-4-2 formation and implented zonal defending, years before Arrigo Sacchi did at AC Milan.

t4268.text: Franco Tancredi made two or three saves otherwise his goal was not put under serious pressure.

t4269.text: Andreas Thom was the only Berlin player capable of inventing something and he had the East German team's best chance with a solo run in the second half.

t4270.text: The Giallorossi dominated this game from start to finish and the East Germans posed little threat on the ball. Roma's movement, especially in possession, was excellent. Dynamo were anything but dynamic. Quite static and lacked ideas going forward.
